attributes.title: Ep. 166 Donald Trump Pt. 5: Thar She Blows
attributes.description: We're back with the penultimate episode in our series on Donald Trump. Tune in to hear Mando tell Paige and Andrea the story of the world's first Trump supporter and all of the craziness that led to Donald becoming president. But do it quietly. Ross Perot might be eavesdropping still.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 166 Donald Trump Pt. 5: Thar She Blows

attributes.title: The Speculation Zone: Insane Clown Posse
attributes.description: If you're a member of the Facebook group or follow any of us on social media you're probably aware that it has been a difficult few weeks for all three of us. We're taking a week to regroup but we will be back next week with the final installment in our current series and a brand new series after that. In the meantime, enjoy one of our favorite Speculation Zone episodes! Whoop whoop!
attributes.display_title: The Speculation Zone: Insane Clown Posse

attributes.title: Capitol Madness: Villain Slow Clap Rhythm
attributes.description: We're choosing to put a pin in our series on Donald Trump while the dust settles. However we wanted to take some time to talk about everything that's been going on the last few weeks. We'll be back next week starting a brand new series on a topic you're gonna love to learn about!
attributes.display_title: Capitol Madness: Villain Slow Clap Rhythm

attributes.title: Ep. 167 Satanic Panic: Swans Get Cancelled (Ft. Blaine Gibson)
attributes.description: We're back with our first non-Trump episode in A WHILE! We're so stoked to be joined by Rooster Teeth's Blaine Gibson to cover the story of America's second witch-hunt, the Satanic Panic! Join us as Paige takes Mando, Andrea, and our resident hell-expert through the beginnings of Satan's life. Kinda.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 167 Satanic Panic: Swans Get Cancelled (Ft. Blaine Gibson)

attributes.title: Ep. 168 Satanic Panic Pt. 2: Build-A-Berg Workshop (Ft. Blaine Gibson)
attributes.description: We're back this week continuing our series on the Satanic Panic with special guest Blaine Gibson! Join us as Paige takes Mando, Andrea, and Blaine through some more recent history of the topic. Back then it was more of a Satanic Anxiety that was quickly growing! But stuff. Gets. Real.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 168 Satanic Panic Pt. 2: Build-A-Berg Workshop (Ft. Blaine Gibson)

attributes.title: Ep. 169 Satanic Panic Pt. 3: Mind Your P’s & Q’s (Ft. Blaine Gibson)
attributes.description: We're back with another installment in our series on The Satanic Panic! Join us as Paige takes Mando, Andrea, and special guest Blaine Gibson through that era where music was filled with reversed satanic messages. Or was it? Somebody should definitely be asking these questions.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 169 Satanic Panic Pt. 3: Mind Your P’s & Q’s (Ft. Blaine Gibson)

attributes.title: Ep. 170 Satanic Panic Pt. 4: Tropical Medicine (Ft. Blaine Gibson)
attributes.description: We're back with another installment in our series on The Satanic Panic! Join us as Paige takes Mando, Andrea, and special guest Blaine Gibson through the dark and confusing history of "repressed memories". Learn all about how Canada has screwed the rest of us over!
attributes.display_title: Ep. 170 Satanic Panic Pt. 4: Tropical Medicine (Ft. Blaine Gibson)

attributes.title: Ep. 171 Satanic Panic Pt. 5: The Kitty Toy
attributes.description: We're back with the final installment in our series on The Satanic Panic. Blaine Gibson couldn't join us for the full episode due to the great Austin Winter Storm of 2021 but he still manages to drop by for a quick cameo. However, you can still join Paige as she takes Mando and Andrea through the final leg in the Panic's history.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 171 Satanic Panic Pt. 5: The Kitty Toy

attributes.title: Ep. 172 Huna: Onde the D?
attributes.description: We're back this week with one heck of a palette cleanser! Join us as Paige takes Mando and Andrea through some very real Hawaiian history followed by some incredibly offensive and incorrect history. Get ready to learn about the religion specifically tailored to divorced step-dads.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 172 Huna: Onde the D?

attributes.title: Ep. 173 The Mandela Effect: Thot Experiment
attributes.description: We're back from another alternate timeline where we were the supreme overlords of Earth. Honestly, it's kind of a bummer to be back as simple humans with no power at all. Oh, well. Join us as Man-dew takes Paige and Andrea through the beliefs of some conspiracy theorists and the basics of quantum mechanics! Trust us, it's way more fun than it sounds.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 173 The Mandela Effect: Thot Experiment

attributes.title: Ep. 174 Strong City: Meat World
attributes.description: We're back with another great episode this week! Join us as Paige takes Mando and Andrea through the story of Strong Town, a weirdo cult led by a trailer park boy who done thought he was Jesus. Aw, shucks, is he gonna be mad when he found out he was wrong.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 174 Strong City: Meat World

attributes.title: Ep. 175 DayLife Army: Mando Ruins Gumby
attributes.description: We're back this week with another buckwild Mando episode. Strap in, and maybe on, as he takes Paige and Andrea through the origins of The DayLife Army. This is one of the strangest and most modern cults we've ever covered and you're in for a wild ride.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 175 DayLife Army: Mando Ruins Gumby

attributes.title: Ep. 176 DayLife Army Pt 2: Detergunt
attributes.description: We're back with part two of our series on The DayLife Army and it's two very weird leaders, Wiz-El and KoA. Join us as Mando takes Paige and Andrea through the groups "Standurds" and the context for why this group was getting so much attention online. It'll bring you back to 2013. Simpler times.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 176 DayLife Army Pt 2: Detergunt

attributes.title: Ep. 177 The DayLife Army Pt. 3: Loads of Cupholders
attributes.description: Hey, everyone. We're here this week with a bit of an odd episode. It's good, don't get me wrong. It's funny, informative, and full of goofs. But we also address a big change happening on the show. For more information feel free to check out our social media accounts. In the meantime, join Mando as he takes Paige through the end of our series on Tumple/The DayLife Army.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 177 The DayLife Army Pt. 3: Loads of Cupholders

attributes.title: Ep. 178 Brad Tyler: Eat a Donut & Hate a Woman (ft. Todd from Horror Virgin)
attributes.description: We've got a very special episode for you this week as we're joined by one of the hosts of our sister show, Horror Virgin! Join us as Paige takes Mando and Todd Schlosser through the rise of a very small often overlooked cult leader named Brad Tyler. This one gets real weird, real fast. But that's always the case when we talk about real s***.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 178 Brad Tyler: Eat a Donut & Hate a Woman (ft. Todd from Horror Virgin)

attributes.title: Web Crawlers Crossover: Valentina De Andrade
attributes.description: We're back this week with a special treat! We're joining forces with the internet sleuths over at Web Crawlers to bring you the story of Valentina De Andrade and her cult of boy-hating weirdos. It doesn't take long for this one to get real wild. You're gonna love it!
attributes.display_title: Web Crawlers Crossover: Valentina De Andrade

attributes.title: Ep. 179 Carlos Castaneda: Mama Mia, Sharks are Stupid!
attributes.description: We're back this week with one of the CRAZIEST stories we've ever covered on the podcast. Join us as Mando takes Paige and our special guest, Todd from Horror Virgin, through the life and education of Carlos Castaneda. His story is one filled with tons of twists and turns and during this two part series you'll be learning the full thing. Strap in. You're not even close to ready.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 179 Carlos Castaneda: Mama Mia, Sharks are Stupid!

attributes.title: Ep. 180 Carlos Castaneda Pt. 2: Dad Went Out for Infinity Cigarettes
attributes.description: We're back for the final episode in our short series on Carlos Castaneda and the practice of Tensegrity. And boy oh boy if you thought last week was crazy you ain't seen nothing yet. Join us as Mando takes Paige and special guest Todd from Horror Virgin/Romancing the Pod through the hilarious and VERY shockingly dark end to our story. Stay tuned to the very end for a special guest appearance.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 180 Carlos Castaneda Pt. 2: Dad Went Out for Infinity Cigarettes

attributes.title: Ep. 181 The Aetherius Society: The Caucacity (ft. Kristal Adams)
attributes.description: Have you ever wondered what a ton of yoga and driving could do for you? Neither have we. It's a weird question. But join us as Paige takes Mando and special guest Kristal Adams through the story of a man who did ask himself this very weird question. If you want more Kristal in your life check out her and Paige's podcast "Black Card Rehab" and consider donating to Mutiny Magazine's Kickstarter.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 181 The Aetherius Society: The Caucacity (ft. Kristal Adams)

attributes.title: Ep. 182 Deprogramming: The Daddy Grace Cinematic Universe (ft. Blaine Gibson)
attributes.description: We're back with another crazy ass story! Join us as Paige takes Mando and special guest Blaine Gibson through the history of cult deprogramming! It's a wild ride and we hope you're ready to learn all about Black Lightning and the DGCU. Coming soon to a movie theater near you.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 182 Deprogramming: The Daddy Grace Cinematic Universe (ft. Blaine Gibson)

attributes.title: Ep. 183 Deprogramming Pt. 2: Danny Karate (ft. Blaine Gibson)
attributes.description: We’re back with another installment in Paige’s series on Cult Deprogramming! Join as she takes Mando and special guest Blern Gerbsen through one of the most action packed stories we’ve covered lately. See you in the dojo, this one gets crazy.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 183 Deprogramming Pt. 2: Danny Karate (ft. Blaine Gibson)

attributes.title: Ep. 184 Deprogramming Pt. 3: Comedy for Food Handlers (ft. Blaine Gibson)
attributes.description: We’re back this week with Ted Patrick's greatest deprogramming hits! Join us as Paige takes Mando and special guest Blaine Gibson through her final episode on Cult Deprogramming. Watch out, once you get your ServSafe certification, there ain't no turning back.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 184 Deprogramming Pt. 3: Comedy for Food Handlers (ft. Blaine Gibson)

attributes.title: Ep. 185 Fiat Lux: Harold Christ (ft. Mikey from Horror Virgin)
attributes.description: We're back this week and we're joined by special guest Michael Randolph from Horror Virgin! Join us as Mando takes Paige and Mikey through the bumpy ride that is Erika Gessler's life. You know what though? Through ups and downs she can always count on her man Harry. Good guy.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 185 Fiat Lux: Harold Christ (ft. Mikey from Horror Virgin)

attributes.title: Ep. 186 Fiat Lux Pt. 2: My Little Phony (ft. Mikey from Horror Virgin)
attributes.description: We're back with the final episode of our two parter on Fiat Lux and their fabulously wacky leader Uriella. Join us as Mando takes Paige and special guest Mikey from Horror Virgin through the group's weird saga of "medicine". And buckle up, this one gets real wild real fast.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 186 Fiat Lux Pt. 2: My Little Phony (ft. Mikey from Horror Virgin)

attributes.title: Ep. 187 Love Has Won: Let’s Get Sheep Faced (ft. Barbara Dunkelman)
attributes.description: Yes, we received your hundreds of emails/tweets/DM's and we're finally here to talk about Love Has Won aka The Most Ambitious McDonalds Manager EVER. This episode has everything, Mummies, God Daddies, and only the most organic drugs and alcohol.
attributes.display_title: Ep. 187 Love Has Won: Let’s Get Sheep Faced (ft. Barbara Dunkelman)

attributes.title: Texas Madness: Paige is a Bread Sorceress
attributes.description: We're taking a week off to recover from an excruciating schedule. But don't worry, we've got a full episode of riffs, goofs, and a few fan Q&A's. Join Paige and Mando for an absolutely wild time and then get hyped for the upcoming series that starts next week!
attributes.display_title: Texas Madness: Paige is a Bread Sorceress

attributes.title: Ep. 188 Symbionese Liberation Army: Pocket Bomb!
attributes.description: We're back, baybee! Hope you're ready for the first part of one of the craziest stories EVER! Join us as Paige takes Mando and special guest Bobby from Science Faction through the origins of Donald Dafreeze who would go on to start the SLA and win the award for "Worst Husband Ever".
attributes.display_title: Ep. 188 Symbionese Liberation Army: Pocket Bomb!
